      "instruction": "<p>Remove your <strong>pineapple</strong> from the can (reserve the juice for later!) and chop roughly</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>chopped pineapple</strong> and cook for 3-4 min on each side or until lightly charred – this is your <strong>charred pineapple</strong></p>",
